-- South Africa Wins Toss, Bats Against Pakistan in World Twenty20
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-28T09:41:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-28/south-africa-wins-toss-bats-against-pakistan-in-world-twenty20.html
South Africa won the toss and will
bat first against Pakistan in their opening Super Eight game at
cricket’s World Twenty20 championship in Colombo,  Sri Lanka .  Australia meets India later today in the second game in
Group 2, also in Colombo.  There two groups of four in the Super Eight with the top
two teams in each advancing to the semifinals. Sri Lanka beat
New Zealand and West Indies defeated defending champion England
in yesterday’s Group 1 openers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
